# if Statements in Python

```python
x = 42

if x < 0:
    print("Negative changed to zero")   # runs if x is less than 0
elif x == 0:
    print("Zero")                       # runs if x equals 0
elif x == 1:
    print("Single")                     # runs if x equals 1
else:
    print("More")                       # runs if no condition matches

# Result:
# More

---

